  "prompt": "Can I catch a strep throat infection from a hug from my girlfriend?",
  "response": "Yes, strep throat can be transmitted through close contact like hugging, kissing, or sharing utensils. The bacteria that cause strep throat (Streptococcus pyogenes) spread through respiratory droplets and saliva. If your girlfriend has an active strep throat infection, you could potentially catch it. To reduce transmission risk:\n\n1. Avoid close contact when she is symptomatic\n2. Encourage her to cover her mouth when coughing/sneezing\n3. Practice good hand hygiene\n4. Have her complete her antibiotic treatment\n5. Wait until she has been on antibiotics for at least 24 hours before close contact\n\nIf you develop symptoms like sore throat, fever, or swollen lymph nodes, consult a healthcare professional.",
